{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 03:03:49.456875", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted solution:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): server_access_router\n- Root cause: http_acl_block\n\nRationale:\nBackend web servers (10.200.0.3–10.200.0.6) are directly reachable from user subnets, allowing HTTP and ICMP access and bypassing the load balancer. DNS and load balancer are healthy. This indicates missing/ineffective L3/L4 access controls at the server access edge; the policy should block direct HTTP from clients to backend servers and force traffic through the load balancer.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1884, "output_tokens": 122, "total_tokens": 2006, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
